sentences: Christopher Steven Brown (also known as CB and Chris Brown; born May 16, 1984, Flint, Michigan) is an American music executive.
In 2009, he left the industry when the market crashed due to the Subprime mortgage crisis.
Brown then changed career and graduated from the Connecticut School of Broadcasting in 2014.
In 2014 and 2015 Brown was the co-host of the Home and Castle Television series.
In March 2020, Brown was nominated in the "Indy Record Executive" category of the WorldWide Radio Summit awards.
